Where your intuition might be pointing

The knight move is interesting because it mixes two principles:
	1.	Structured space (the grid)
	2.	Non-local jumps

Many modern systems—especially networks and information structures—behave this way. They aren’t purely local like simple geometry.

You could view the knight move as a simple example of a rule that reshapes connectivity in a system.

