A neat way to see it

If you imagine a chessboard as coordinates (x,y), a knight step is one of these transformations:

(x,y) \rightarrow (x \pm 2, y \pm 1)

or

(x,y) \rightarrow (x \pm 1, y \pm 2)

These moves create a distinctive network of reachable positions.

